Rescuers on Saturday recovered two bodies from the ruins of a three-storey building under construction, which collapsed in the Yaba area of Lagos. This was confirmed by the Director-General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, Dr Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu.  The incident happened on Akanbi Crescent, close to the University of Lagos. First responders from the Lagos State Emergency Management Agency arrived at the scene to begin rescue operations.


 
